BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:V5PjPeujs8n6VdATt7m_G
SUMMARY:Forterra Fridays: April 2026
DTSTAMP:20260406T054319Z
DTSTART:20260417T200000Z
DESCRIPTION:Forterra Fridays: April 2026 \n\nFriday\, Apr. 17\, 2026\, 1:00
	 pm to 3:30 pm \n\nWe’re excited to invite you to volunteer with us for a 
	special Earth Month event at Duwamish Hill Preserve\, a Tukwila park provi
	ding critical wildlife habitat and public trails in the middle of an indus
	trial area. Join us on Friday\, April 17th\, from 1:00 pm to 3:30 pm\, to 
	restore essential wildlife habitat by removing Himalayan blackberries that
	 threaten our local native trees\, shrubs\, and groundcover. Established n
	ative plants benefit local wildlife\, improve water quality\, and enhance 
	air quality.  \n\nYou will also gain valuable insights into ecological res
	toration and our innovative approach to land conservation. We’ll start wit
	h a walk of the site and Earth Day-themed trivia and have restoration prof
	essionals on hand to answer questions about plants\, restoration\, and the
	 Green Tukwila Partnership and Forterra.  \n\nWhat we are doing: The Prese
	rve now includes an outdoor classroom area\, the Cultural Garden\, an enha
	nced trail system\, and continued restoration opportunities for volunteers
	. We’ll be removing the blackberry to ensure the trees\, shrubs\, and grou
	ndcover plants can thrive.   It’s a great opportunity to learn about Forte
	rra’s innovative approach to land conservation\, including its role in saf
	eguarding the Duwamish Hill Preserve.  \n\nWhat to bring: Please dress for
	 the weather \\(in layers to stay warm/dry\\). Snacks\, drinks\, tools\, a
	nd gloves will all be provided. \n\nWhere to park: Park in the nearby park
	ing lot at Duwamish Hill Preserve. Signs direct you from the parking lot t
	o where we will meet. \n\n \n\nDate and Time: Friday\, April 17\, 2026\, 1
	:00 –3:30 PM  \n\nRegister and learn more here.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcit
	y.com/events/#/details/forterra-fridays-april-2026/17979521/2026-04-17T00\
	n\nFrom SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/forterra-fridays-april-20
	26/17979521/2026-04-17T00
LOCATION:Duwamish Hill Preserve\, 3800 South 115th Street\, Tukwila\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:yfNci8RvIRb63laEBT6k8
SUMMARY:Pilates for Gardeners
DTSTAMP:20260406T054319Z
DTSTART:20260417T210000Z
DESCRIPTION:Taught by Jo Anne Iaciofano. Grab your mat\, kick off your shoe
	s\, and join this Pilates-inspired class to improve body movement\, core s
	trength\, and muscle control. This beginner’s friendly class\, using mind-
	body connection and breath\, will take you through a series of exercises w
	ith an emphasis on technique and fluidity. We will focus on those areas mo
	st stressed during gardening by using your core to power the muscles incre
	asing your energy and endurance. All levels are welcome. Wear comfortable 
	clothing and be prepared to workout barefoot. Please bring a yoga or Pilat
	es mat\, towel\, and water. This class will take place in the Aaron Educat
	ion Center.  $17.50 BBGS Member/$25 Non-Member.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcit
	y.com/events/#/details/pilates-for-gardeners/17923217/2026-04-17T00\n\nFro
	m SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/pilates-for-gardeners/179
	23217/2026-04-17T00
LOCATION:Bellevue Botanical Garden\, 12001 Main St\, Bellevue\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-sports
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Sports & Outdoors
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
